## Feeding Guide {#feeding}

Goldfish are omnivores with a preference for plant matter and invertebrates. Their high metabolism requires regular feeding but overfeeding is the most common mistake.

**Recommended foods:**
- High-quality sinking pellets — goldfish should not be fed floating foods (gulping air while eating causes digestive issues and buoyancy problems)
- Gel foods (homemade or commercial) — ideal for fancy varieties prone to digestive issues
- Frozen foods: Daphnia, brine shrimp, bloodworms (in moderation — high in protein but low nutritional diversity)
- Vegetables: blanched peas (de-shelled), spinach, zucchini — goldfish benefit from plant matter in the diet

**Live foods from [Blackwater Aquatics](https://blackwateraquatics.ca/collections/live-foods):**
- **Live Daphnia** — excellent supplemental food; the digestive enzyme content supports gut health and reduces constipation, a common fancy goldfish problem
- **Live Scuds** — good enrichment and protein source for larger fancy goldfish

**Feeding frequency:** 1–2 times daily, amount consumed within 2–3 minutes. Fast one day per week. Overfeeding is the leading cause of goldfish digestive issues and water quality problems.

