## Health and Disease {#health}

**Swim Bladder Disorder:** Extremely common in fancy goldfish. The compressed body shape of double-tail varieties crowds the internal organs, including the swim bladder. Symptoms: floating, sinking, listing. Treatment: fast for 3 days, then feed live daphnia; switch to sinking foods exclusively; consider gel food diet.

**Fin Rot:** Bacterial erosion of fin tissue from poor water quality. Improve conditions; antibiotic treatment for severe cases.

**Ich:** Standard temperature and medication treatment.

**Flukes (Gill Flukes, Skin Flukes):** Common in goldfish, especially from ponds. Symptoms: flashing, rubbing, rapid breathing. Treat with praziquantel.

**Dropsy:** Pinecone-scale protrusion and swelling from systemic bacterial infection or organ failure. Very difficult to treat; improve water quality and isolate immediately.

**Constipation and Bloat:** Very common in fancy varieties. Prevention: varied diet, sinking foods, regular fasting, and [live Daphnia](https://blackwateraquatics.ca/collections/live-foods) supplementation.

